item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: wpengine
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http://dci-template.dcistage.wpengine.com.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you have an account and you log in to this site, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

item.dc:creator: wpengine
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row][vc_column][ieee_heading text="Embed a Form on Your Site" heading="h1"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Please use a third-party service such as Google Forms, SurveyMonkey, MailChimp, or Constant Contact to include email forms and signup forms on your website. Instructions:
  • Google Forms
  • SurveyMonkey
  • Mailchimp
  • Constant Contact
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="261" img_size="medium" style="vc_box_border_circle" css_animation="fadeIn"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543941846216{margin-top: 20px !important;}" el_id="google-form-inst"][vc_column][vc_separator][ieee_heading text="Google Forms" heading="h2"][vc_column_text]You can embed Google Docs, Sheets, Slides, and Forms into your website as long as they are public.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row gap="10" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/3"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fdocs%2Fanswer%2F183965%3Fco%3DGENIE.Platform%253DDesktop%26hl%3Den|title:How%20To%3A%20Make%20a%20Google%20Doc%20Public|target:%20_blank|" type="a"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fdocs%2Fanswer%2F183965%23embed_files|title:How%20To%3A%20Embed%20a%20Google%20Doc|target:%20_blank|" type="a"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543942247206{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Paste the HTML copy provided by Google into a "Text Block" element on this site. Be sure to paste the text into the Text editor, not the Visual editor, as marked in the screenshot. Save your changes in the text area as well as on the page to see your form on the front end.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="289" img_size="full" style="vc_box_border" css=".vc_custom_1543942337317{border-radius: 1px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543942600885{margin-top: 20px !important;}" el_id="surveymonkey-inst"][vc_column][vc_separator][ieee_heading text="SurveyMonkey" heading="h2"][vc_column_text]Surveys can be embedded on your website by using the Website Collectors option in SurveyMonkey. Note: Surveys embedded with the Website Code are not accessible on mobile devices or tablets. If you expect that many visitors will be using mobile devices, consider linking out to the survey instead.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row gap="10" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/3"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.surveymonkey.com%2Farticles%2Fen_US%2Fkb%2FWebsite-Collector|title:How%20To%3A%20Embed%20a%20SurveyMonkey%20Survey|target:%20_blank|" type="a"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543942247206{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Paste the HTML copy provided by SurveyMonkey into a "Text Block" element on this site. Be sure to paste the text into the Text editor, not the Visual editor, as marked in the screenshot. Save your changes in the text area as well as on the page to see your form on the front end.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="289" img_size="full" style="vc_box_border" css=".vc_custom_1543942337317{border-radius: 1px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543950590586{margin-top: 20px !important;}" el_id="mailchimp-inst"][vc_column][vc_separator][ieee_heading text="Mailchimp" heading="h2"][vc_column_text]After it's been created within Mailchimp, you can embed mailing list signup forms on your website.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row gap="10" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/3"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fmailchimp.com%2Fhelp%2Fadd-a-signup-form-to-your-website%2F|title:How%20To%3A%20Embed%20a%20Mailchimp%20Signup%20Form|target:%20_blank|" type=""][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543942247206{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Paste the HTML copy provided by Mailchimp into a "Text Block" element on this site. Be sure to paste the text into the Text editor, not the Visual editor, as marked in the screenshot. Save your changes in the text area as well as on the page to see your form on the front end.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="289" img_size="full" style="vc_box_border" css=".vc_custom_1543942337317{border-radius: 1px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543951117192{margin-top: 20px !important;}" el_id="constantcontact-inst"][vc_column][vc_separator][ieee_heading text="Constant Contact" heading="h2"][vc_column_text]You can embed a mailing list sign up form from Constant Contact after it's been created. Note:Only inline forms are supported.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row gap="10" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/2"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fknowledgebase.constantcontact.com%2Farticles%2FKnowledgeBase%2F18265-Create-a-Sign-Up-Form-with-the-new-sign-up-form-experience%3Fic%3Dcomm_blog%26lang%3Den_US|title:How%20To%3A%20Create%20an%20Inline%20Constant%20Contact%20Form|target:%20_blank|" type=""][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][ieee_button color="btn-primary" block="true" href="url:https%3A%2F%2Fknowledgebase.constantcontact.com%2Farticles%2FKnowledgeBase%2F18053-activating-and-installing-your-sign-up-form%3Flang%3Den_US|title:How%20To%3A%20Activate%20%26%20Install%20a%20Constant%20Contact%20Form|target:%20_blank|" type=""][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1543942247206{margin-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Paste the HTML copy provided by Constant Contact into a "Text Block" element on this site. item.title: 2018 2nd International Conference on Informatics and Computational Sciences (ICICoS)
item.dc:creator: ieeeattend
item.content:encoded: The 2nd International Conference on Informatics and Computational Sciences (ICICoS 2018) aims to provide a platform for Researchers, Academicians, Professionals, Engineers, and also students to share their research ideas and results of research especially in the field of informatics, computational science and related field. The highlight of ICICoS 2018 is The Challenge of Industry 4.0 and Its Impact on Society. This highlight is selected inline with Indonesian Goverment Policy in Industry Sector. In addition, this highlight is chosen so that researchers, Academicians, Professionals, Engineers, and also students are encouraged to perform research on this field.
